      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BERNARDO'S QUEEN (7) is progressing well scoring last time out (27.75) at Bendigo and bringing up her 5th career win. Form at the trip excellent including two wins. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Can measure up again. O'KEEFE (1) is a quick beginner who bombed the start last time and missed the frame, finishing fifth (25.60) in a Grade 4/5 at Shepparton. Placed the start prior (25.60) at Shepparton after firing out of the boxes. Has a good record at this journey. Has a strong record out of this box with four wins and a minor placing from six starts. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. PAW LOVISA (2) was well fancied last time over 515m at Sandown but in traffic and fell. Must include in calculations. TRENDY ART (3) is a last start winner who rates one of the chances again.",
